The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Godrej Consumer Products has reported a 57 per cent jump in after-tax profit at Rs 27.10 crore for the first quarter of the current financial year. The company board has recommended a 75 per cent interim dividend for shareholders. Total sales of the company has grown 23 per cent at Rs 167.70 crore during the three months. The profit growth jacks up the earning per share to Rs 4.79 from Rs 3.05 during the same period last year.

 Voltas has reported a 29.16 per cent increase in net profit at Rs 50.41 crore in 2004-05 compared with Rs 39.03 crore in the previous year. The net sales increased by 8.38 per cent to Rs 1441.43 crore compared with Rs 1329.94 crore. The company board has also recommended a dividend of 50 per cent for the year ended March 31, including a Special Golden Jubilee dividend of 15 per cent.

 Alstom Ltd has reported a 44 per cent rise in earnings for the first quarter of the current fiscal. The company has clocked a net profit of Rs 9.05 crore for the first three months ended June 30, 2005 compared with Rs 6.28 crore in the year-ago period. 

 Century Textiles amp; Industries Ltd (CTIL) has posted a 131.65 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 46.10 crore for the quarter ended June 30, 2005 compared with Rs 19.90 crore in the corresponding quarter in 2004-05. Total income has increased 11.26 per cent at Rs 671.37 crore.

 ABB has registered a net profit at Rs 43.60 crore for the second quarter ended June 30, 2005, up 42.43 per cent from Rs 30.61 recorded during the corresponding quarter last year. The power and automation technology provider?s total income has increased 27.65 per cent to Rs 672.98 crore from Rs 527.17 crore in the year-ago period.

 Crisil Ltd has reported a 72 per cent rise in net profit for the first quarter ended June 30 at Rs 5.57 crore against Rs 3.24 crore in the same period last year. The rating agency?s consolidated total income during the quarter rose to Rs 37.47 crore from Rs 25.29 crore.

